SetString english right_helmet_flair_hul_description "The Hardened Uplink (HUL) is an external helmet attachment compatible with helmet variants of the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor."
SetString english right_helmet_flair_mp_romeo "ODST (Buck)"
SetString english right_helmet_flair_mp_romeo_description "Worn by Gunnery Sergeant Edward Buck of Alpha-Nine."
SetString english right_helmet_flair_ua "ua"
SetString english right_helmet_flair_ua_description "The Hardened Uplink (ua) is an external helmet attachment compatible with helmet variants of the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor."
SetString english rightshoulder "RIGHT SHOULDER"
SetString english spartan_body_bungie "Grenadier"
SetString english spartan_body_bungie_description "The [G] prototype was the test bed for incorporating shield technology with MJOLNIR PAA."
SetString english spartan_body_cobra "UA/Base Security"
SetString english spartan_body_cobra_description "Keep it simple; leave everything you don't absolutely need at the CP."
SetString english spartan_body_default "Mark V [B]"
SetString english spartan_body_default_description "Entered service in 2551; UNICOM/ SPECWAR/ GroupTHREE has been the sole adopter."
SetString english spartan_body_intruder "Assault/Sapper"
SetString english spartan_body_intruder_description "Broadly speaking, sappers are equally at home building things as they are blowing them up."
SetString english spartan_body_katana "UA/ODST"
SetString english spartan_body_katana_description "Many technologies initially developed for MJOLNIR have seen widespread adoption."
SetString english spartan_body_marathon "Security"
SetString english spartan_body_marathon_description "Manufactured in 2528 at the Misrah Armories Facility on Mars in preparation for the second class of SPARTAN IIs, the Mark V(m) variant was mothballed until February 2551, when it was refitted and upgraded."
SetString english spartan_body_markv "Mark V"
SetString english spartan_body_markv_description "Originally issued in August 2542, all extant Mjolnir Mark V Powered Assault Armor has been upgraded with current-issue internal components and modified to be compatible with all current-issue armor variants."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_commando "Commando"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_commando_description "Anything you don't have, you can find in the field. Anything you can't find, you didn't need anyway."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_counter_assault "Counter Assault"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_counter_assault_description "Supplemental Armor, Torso, MJOLNIR Mk. V; with increased storage capacity."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_dutch "ODST (Dutch)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_dutch_description "Worn by Corporal Taylor H. Dutch Miles of Alpha-Nine."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_exo "EXO/TSCS"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_exo_description "Modified for exo-atmospheric engagements, with onboard Tactical Signals Intelligence Collection System."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_hp "HP/HALO"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_hp_description "Supplemental armor with hard points for High-Altitude Low-Opening gear."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_marine "Marine"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_marine_description "Normally worn by UNSC Marines, This armor has been adapted to function with MARK V armor systems."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_mark_iv "MARK IV"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_mark_iv_description "The Mark IV MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor was the first version of the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor series. The suit was issued to Spartan-II commandos on November 27, 2525."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_orion "orion"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_orion_description "Project ORION had ambitious plans for complete super-soldier weapon systems, but only Dr. Halsey had the vision and genius to bring both hardware and wetware to fruition."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_parafoil "Parafoil"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_parafoil_description "Try to remember on your next jump that it's FEET first into hell."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven1 "ODST (TAC)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven1_description "The ensemble of choice when you need to stomp the Covenant, but on a budget."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven2 "ODST (HVY)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven2_description "As they say during ODST screening: the best defense is an overwhelming offense."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven3 "ODST (COM)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven3_description "The ensemble for an ODST that wants to reach out and touch someone with artillery and ortillery support."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven4 "ODST (DEMO)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_raven4_description "Obstacles to progress are measured by the number of satchel charges they rate."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_romeo "ODST (Romeo)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_romeo_description "Worn by Lance Corporal Kojo Romeo Agu of Alpha-Nine."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_rookie "ODST (Rookie)"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_rookie_description "Worn by Lance Corporal Rookie of Alpha-Nine."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_spi "SPI"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_spi_description "This variant is a modified SPI armor and compatible with the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor Mark VI. It incorporates the latest in software-definable deception jammers."
SetString english spartan_body_mp_tactical "Tactical/LRP"
SetString english spartan_body_mp_tactical_description "If you are going to be out there for a long time, you might as well take everything."
SetString english spartan_body_ninja "UA/Multi-Threat"
SetString english spartan_body_ninja_description "Supplemental Armor, Torso, MJOLNIR Mk. V."
SetString english spartan_body_regulator "Collar/Breacher"
SetString english spartan_body_regulator_description "Kick it in; section it off; lay them out."
SetString english spartan_body_ryu "Tactical/Recon"
SetString english spartan_body_ryu_description "Everything you need to find everything you need to find out."
SetString english spartan_body_scout "Tactical/Patrol"
SetString english spartan_body_scout_description "Don't take anything you don't need; you're going to want to stay light on your feet."
SetString english spartan_helmet_default "Mark V [B]"
SetString english spartan_helmet_default_description "Entered service in 2551; UNICOM/ SPECWAR/ GroupTHREE has been the sole adopter."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_air_assault "Air Assault"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_air_assault_description "Entered service in 2535; the MJOLNIR/AA variant is exclusive to Army airborne units."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_bungie "Bungie"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_bungie_description "Forged in the flames of passion and perseverance. Go forth and represent."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_cobra "CQB"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_cobra_description "Developed at Beweglichr\u00fcstungsysteme and tested at the UNSC's Special Warfare Center."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_collar "Collar/Grenadier [UA]"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_collar_description "Up-armored variant of the MJOLNIR [G] prototype."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_commando "Commando"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_commando_description "Developed at the UNSC's Special Warfare Center, this helmet is compatible with all armor systems. The Mk.V/K helmet was developed at the Special Warfare Centre in Songnam, Hanguk."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_cqc "CQC"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_cqc_description "Entered service in 2548; standard equipment for boarding actions and MOUT."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_emile "Emile"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_emile_description "The EVA helmet was developed using data gathered from the Summa Space Incident. This specific helmet has had a skull carved into the visor by Emile-A239."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_grd "GRD"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_grd_description "The AKIS helmet and associated components were highly classified, leading some operatives to question its very existence."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_grenadier "Grenadier"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_grenadier_description "The Mk.IV[G] variant is an up-armored prototype based on the basic Mk.IV helmet."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_gungnir "Gungnir"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_gungnir_description "In Norse mythology, Gungnir is Odin's magical spear, which is an infallibly accurate weapon. The GUNGNIR helmet has only one video camera eye on one side of the face; in Norse mythology, Odin also had one eye. This is a theme of the Spartan armor systems as MJOLNIR is the name of Thor's hammer."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_h2aodst "ODST (Alpha)"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_h2aodst_description "Earliest version of the Orbital Drop Shock Trooper armor developed by MAMS of Poseidon Industries."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_haunted "haunted"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_haunted_description "Happy friggin' Halloween!"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_hazop "Hazop"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_hazop_description "The HAZOP armor utilizes a specialized material that helps protect the user from heightened exposure to radiation that normal Mjolnir suits cannot. HAZOP also employs a unique technology to process and manufacture oxygen in highly toxic conditions."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_intruder "EVA"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_intruder_description "The EVA helmet was developed using data gathered from the Summa Space Incident."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_jfo "JFO"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_jfo_description "Beweglichr\u00fcstungsysteme was home to many projects attached to the MJOLNIR program."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_marathon "Security"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_marathon_description "All (M) variant helmets have been upgraded to be compatible with all current issue armor."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_mariner "Mariner"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_mariner_description "Standard MARINER suite is optimised for Sabre, Baselard and Nandao flight systems."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_mark_iv "MARK IV"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_mark_iv_description "The Mark IV MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor was the first version of the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor series. The suit was issued to Spartan-II commandos on November 27, 2525."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_mark_vii "Mark VII"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_mark_vii_description "Materials Group evolutionary design study that eventually formed the basis of the production Mk. VII."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_markv "Mark V"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_markv_description "The Mk. V helmet is essentially the Mk. IV upgraded to function with MJOLNIR's new shield system."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_military_police "Military Police"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_military_police_description "Previously available only to Beta-5 security teams and select Army rapid-reaction forces, Military Police helmets have found a home with Spartan-IV fireteams that require its hardened uplink, command network module, and remote sensor controller."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_ninja "Recon"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_ninja_description "Data gathered from these field tests will be used to improve the final production model."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_odst "ODST"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_odst_description "Many technologies initially developed for MJOLNIR have gained widespread adoption."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_operator "Operator"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_operator_description "The B5D Facility has been the site of many unique development programs."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_orion "Orion"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_orion_description "Project ORION had ambitious plans for complete super-soldier weapon systems, but only Dr. Halsey had the vision and genius to bring both hardware and wetware to fruition."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_pilot "Pilot"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_pilot_description "Although it bears some similarities to the SPI helmet, they are purely cosmetic in nature."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven1 "ODST (TAC)"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven1_description "The ensemble of choice when you need to stomp the Covenant, but on a budget."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven2 "ODST (HVY)"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven2_description "As they say during ODST screening: the best defense is an overwhelming offense."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven3 "ODST (COMM)"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven3_description "The ensemble for an ODST that wants to reach out and touch someone with artillery and ortillery support."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven4 "ODST (DEMO)"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_raven4_description "Obstacles to progress are measured by the number of satchel charges they rate."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_regulator "EOD"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_regulator_description "EOD helmets were designed to significantly reduce the likelihood of decapitation."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_rogue "Mark VI"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_rogue_description "This is the prototype for the Integrated Communications Helmet, MJOLNIR Mk. VI."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_ryu "Samurai"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_ryu_description "Incorperates the latest generation of situational awareness tactical software and cognition-enhancing neural interlinks."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_scout "Scout"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_scout_description "The MJOLNIR VI/S variant was developed and tested at the ONI's Ordnance Testing Facility."
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_spi "SPI"
SetString english spartan_helmet_mp_spi_description "This variant is a modified SPI armor and compatible with the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor Mark VI. It incorporates the latest in software-definable deception jammers."
SetString english spartan_knee_fj/para "fj/para"
SetString english spartan_knee_fj/para_description "Designed specifically for airborne units; maximum protection, minimum weight."
SetString english spartan_knee_k_base "base"
SetString english spartan_knee_k_base_description "."
SetString english spartan_knee_k_grenadier "grenadier"
SetString english spartan_knee_k_grenadier_description "The MJOLNIR[G] prototype informed all subsequent supplemental armor development programs."
SetString english spartan_knee_k_gungnir "k_gungnir"
SetString english spartan_knee_k_gungnir_description "The GUNGNIR Program also produced many supplementary armor systems."
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_orion "ORION"
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_orion_description "Rigorous testing of the greaves was undertaken by candidate 029 on the red plains of Mars."
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven1 "odst (TAC)"
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven1_description "The ensemble of choice when you need to stomp the Covenant, but on a budget."
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven2 "odst (HVY)"
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven2_description "As they say during ODST screening: the best defense is an overwhelming offense."
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven3 "odst (COMM)"
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven3_description "The ensemble for an ODST that wants to reach out and touch someone with artillery and ortillery support."
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven4 "odst (DEMO)"
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_raven4_description "Obstacles to progress are measured by the number of satchel charges they rate."
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_spi "SPI"
SetString english spartan_knee_mp_spi_description "This variant is a modified SPI armor and compatible with the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor Mark VI. It incorporates the latest in software-definable deception jammers."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_bungie "Bungie"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_bungie_description "Forged in the flames of passion and perseverance. Go forth and represent."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_cobra "JFO"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_cobra_description "Designed and tested at Beweglichr\u00fcstungsysteme of Essen, Deutschland."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_cqc "CQC"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_cqc_description "Developed and tested at UNSC facilities in Essen and Songnam, respectively."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_default "Mark V [B]"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_default_description "Entered service in 2551; UNICOM/ SPECWAR/ GroupTHREE has been the sole adopter."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_eva "EVA"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_eva_description "Developed at the UNSC's Low/Zero Gravity Testing Facility on Ganymede."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_grenadier "Grenadier"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_grenadier_description "The MJOLNIR[G] prototype informed all subsequent supplemental armor development programs."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_gungnir "GUNGNIR"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_gungnir_description "The Supplemental Armor, Pauldron, MJOLNIR Mk.V[G] was developed as part of the GUNGNIR Program."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_hazop "HAZOP"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_hazop_description "Some operations are considered hazardous even for a fully armored Spartan."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_intruder "FJ/PARA"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_intruder_description "Designed specifically for airborne units; maximum protection, minimum weight."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_jumpjet "Jump Jet"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_jumpjet_description "Early prototype safety restraints for use with extant Jump Jet equipment."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_marathon "ODST"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_marathon_description "Many technologies initially developed for MJOLNIR have gained widespread adoption."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mark_v "Mark V"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mark_v_description "Issued in November 2551, it is compatible with all powered and semi-powered armor systems."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_markv "Mark V"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_markv_description "Originally issued in August 2542, all extant Mark V deltoid protection has been modified to be compatible with current-issue Mjolnir Powered Assault Armor."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_mark_iv "MARK IV"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_mark_iv_description "The Mark IV MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor was the first version of the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor series. The suit was issued to Spartan-II commandos on November 27, 2525."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_mickey "ODST (Mickey)"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_mickey_description "Worn by Private First Class Michael Mickey Crespo of Alpha-Nine."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_orion "orion"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_orion_description "ORION hardware development studies provided useful data for ensuring both range of motion and high levels of protection on later MJOLNIR designs."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven1 "ODST (TAC)"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven1_description "The ensemble of choice when you need to stomp the Covenant, but on a budget."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven2 "ODST (HVY)"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven2_description "As they say during ODST screening: the best defense is an overwhelming offense."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven3 "ODST (COM)"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven3_description "The ensemble for an ODST that wants to reach out and touch someone with artillery and ortillery support."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven4 "ODST (DEMO)"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_raven4_description "Obstacles to progress are measured by the number of satchel charges they rate."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_romeo "ODST (Romeo)"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_romeo_description "Worn by Lance Corporal Kojo Romeo Agu of Alpha-Nine."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_spi "SPI"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_mp_spi_description "This variant is a modified SPI armor and compatible with the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor Mark VI. It incorporates the latest in software-definable deception jammers."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_ninja "Recon"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_ninja_description "The MJOLNIR[R] prototype reduces armor silhouette without decreasing survivability."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_operator "Operator"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_operator_description "Developed for the Beta-5 Asymmetrical Action Group at ONI's Ordnance Testing Facility."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_regulator "SECURITY"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_regulator_description "The Supplemental Armor, Pauldron, MJOLNIR(M) variant was originally manufactured in 2528."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_ryu "Commando"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_ryu_description "The MJOLNIR Mk. V/K variant was developed at the UNSC's Special Warfare Center."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_scout "Scout"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_scout_description "The SCOUT and RECON projects were run as independent parallel projects intended to develop a single variant of the Mjolnir Powered Assault Armor with stealth capabilities."
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_security "UA/Base Security"
SetString english spartan_leftshoulder_security_description "Lightweight supplemental shoulder armor."
SetString english spartan_mp_marine "Marine"
SetString english spartan_mp_marine_description "Marine pouch."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder "Mark V [B]"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_bungie "Bungie"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_bungie_description "Forged in the flames of passion and perseverance. Go forth and represent."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_cobra "JFO"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_cobra_description "Designed and tested at Beweglichr\u00fcstungsysteme of Essen, Deutschland."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_cqc "CQC"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_cqc_description "Developed and tested at UNSC facilities in Essen and Songnam, respectively."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_default "Mark V [B]"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_default_description "Entered service in 2551; UNICOM/ SPECWAR/ GroupTHREE has been the sole adopter"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_eva "EVA"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_eva_description "Developed at the UNSC's Low/Zero Gravity Testing Facility on Ganymede."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_grenadier "Grenadier"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_grenadier_description "The MJOLNIR[G] prototype informed all subsequent supplemental armor development programs."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_gungnir "GUNGNIR"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_gungnir_description "The Supplemental Armor, Pauldron, MJOLNIR Mk.V[G] was developed as part of the GUNGNIR Program."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_hazop "HAZOP"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_hazop_description "Some operations are considered hazardous even for a fully armored Spartan."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_intruder "FJ/PARA"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_intruder_description "Designed specifically for airborne units; maximum protection, minimum weight."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_jumpjet "Jump Jet"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_jumpjet_description "Early prototype safety restraints for use with extant Jump Jet equipment."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_marathon "ODST"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_marathon_description "Many technologies initially developed for MJOLNIR have gained widespread adoption."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_mark_v "Mark V"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_mark_v_description "Issued in November 2551, it is compatible with all powered and semi-powered armor systems"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_markv "Mark V"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_markv_description "Originally issued in August 2542, all extant Mark V deltoid protection has been modified to be compatible with current-issue Mjolnir Powered Assault Armor."
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_mp_mark_iv "MARK IV"
SetString english spartan_rightshoulder_mp_mark_iv_description "The Mark IV MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor was the first version of the MJOLNIR Powered Assault Armor series. The suit was issued to Spartan-II commandos on November 27, 2525."
